Do Emotions Have Unique 
Physiological Signatures?
• Intuition holds that emotions differ from 
one another in their bodily 
manifestations (e.g., pride, disgust, 
anger, sadness, fear).
• Language supports this common sense 
idea (e.g., “She got hot and bothered,”
“You make my blood boil,” He’s just 
letting off steam”).

